    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#paci2011"/>, p. <citedRange>268</citedRange> and fig. 13, n. 4, 5, 7</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>61.1555, 1-4</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>115400</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#inglese2013"/>, p. <citedRange>234</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>63.1718</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="#gasparini-rosamilia2016"/>, pp. <citedRange>190-195</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>66.2322</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <div type="textpart" n="a">
                <ab> 
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Λάμπις">Λάμπις</name> 
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Κλεόξενος">Κλεοξέ<supplied reason="lost">νω</supplied></name></persName></persName>
                 </ab>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" n="b">
                    <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Στράτων">Στράτων</name> 
                                 <persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Κλεόξενος">Κλεοξένω</name></persName></persName>
                    </ab>
                </div>
                </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>a) Lampis fils de Kléoxénos.
               b) Stratôn fils de Kléoxénos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>a) Lampis son of Kleoxenos.
               b) Straton son of Kleoxenos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>a) Lampis figlio di Kleoxenos.
               b) Straton figlio di Kleoxenos.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Belonging to the well-known group of <foreign rend="italic">escharai</foreign> inscribed with personal names mentioning the 'owners' of the altar, on which they brought offerings for
                an unknown deity, this one differs from the others by its monumentality and by the fact that two brothers inscribed their names on its lateral side and not
                in front.</p>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
